Future Improvements

* Add proper error handling
  Implement try-except blocks for model loading and predictions to prevent app crashes and display user-friendly error messages.

* Implement input validation
  Add validation checks for all input fields (e.g., realistic ranges for blood pressure, cholesterol, etc.) to ensure accurate predictions.

* Handle missing (NaN) values
  Add preprocessing steps to detect and handle missing values in bulk uploads (e.g., imputation or validation warnings).

* Optimize model loading
  Use caching (`st.cache_resource`) to load models only once, improving app performance and reducing response time.

* Improve UI/UX design
  Enhance the interface with better layout, icons, tooltips, and styling for a more professional look.

* Add probability scores
  Display prediction probabilities (confidence levels) instead of only binary output for better interpretability.

* Column name-based prediction
  Replace column index-based logic with column name mapping to avoid errors due to column order changes.

* Add detailed error messages
  Provide clear feedback for incorrect inputs, wrong file formats, or missing columns in uploaded files.

* Support multiple file formats
  Extend bulk upload support to Excel files (.xlsx) in addition to CSV.

* Add data visualization for predictions
  Show charts (e.g., distribution of predictions, risk categories) for bulk uploaded data.

* Improve scalability
  Optimize code to handle larger datasets efficiently without performance degradation.

* Model retraining capability
  Add functionality to retrain models with new data directly from the app.

* Deploy with backend/database
  Integrate a database to store user inputs and prediction history for analysis.

* Add authentication system
  Implement login/signup functionality for secure and personalized access.

* Mobile responsiveness
  Improve responsiveness for better usability on mobile devices.

* Add API integration
  Convert the model into an API for integration with other applications.

* Enhance model performance
  Experiment with advanced models and hyperparameter tuning to improve accuracy.

* Add explainability (XAI)
  Integrate tools like SHAP or LIME to explain model predictions.

* Logging and monitoring
  Implement logging to track errors and monitor app performance.

* Docker support for deployment
  Containerize the application for easier and more scalable deployment.
